I keep thinking back to when the media went nuts over Caroline and Harry....How he stood up for Caroline when they ended their relationship & he asked everyone to stop being mean to her. He can be proud he was loyal and protective - somethinng she clearly felt she lacked in her darkest hours. I've always thought many of his songs were inspired by his friendship with her and unresolved feelings he hasn't been able to shake free. The lyrics of this song fit so well with Carolines heartbreaking passing, I wonder if it was written with her in mind. He would've known how difficult life was for Caroline - having a mutual close friend in Louise Teasdale (who, according to some reports, was the best friend who was staying with Caroline the day she died). He's done a lot of grieviing these past few years. Awful for such a beautiful soul. I hope the people around him are present for him during these challenging times. And I hope the other 1D lads look after each other privately to give each other the strength to get through it.
